==Introduction==

To simplify the development, management and maintenance of multiple '''Wiki Instances''', comprehensive '''Wiki ecosystem''' was created.

The foundation of this ecosystem is a '''Wiki Platform''', software framework which allows to create, run and manage multiple ''Wiki Instances'' in a protected environment.

To simplify the development and maintenance of Wiki Instance '''content''', the '''Wiki Automation Tool''' was created.

The Wiki maintainers are not required to develop and maintain Wiki pages (forms, templates, etc.), but instead define a domain specific logical '''Wiki Model'''
which describes desired Wiki functionality in an XML file.

The Wiki Automation Tool based on the XML Wiki Model automatically generates and deploys '''Application Pages''' to given Wiki Instance, providing required functionality for the users.


